    dc:description "Fig. 3. Homotropus klopfsteinae sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (NHRS-HEVA000011629). Habitus, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5578742/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5578746>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Homotropus klopfsteinae sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (NHRS-HEVA000011629). A. Head anterior view. B. First and second tergites, dorsal view. C. Tergites 2–7, dorsal view. D. Scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view. E. Head and mesosoma, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5578746/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5578764>
    dc:description "Fig. 13. Seashore along the Baltic sea at Haparanda Santasaari, type locality for Homotropus klopfsteinae sp. nov. Photo: Nils Ryrholm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5578764/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5578735>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Bayesian phylogenetic reconstruction based on a four-gene dataset from Klopfstein et al. (2011). The two new taxa Homotropus klopfsteinae sp. nov. and Woldstedtius aureotibialis sp. nov. were included in the dataset by their barcoding region (CO1). Values next to nodes are posterior probabilities, with asterisks representing maximum clade support." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5578735/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

